com.avaya.csta.binding

Class GetCallInformationResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.GetCallInformationResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GetCallInformationResponse
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Response to a GetCallInformation Request.

    The GetCallInformationResponse has these parameters:

    GetCallInformationResponse Parameters
    stationName Always provided The name administered for this device.
    callId Always provided Holds the call ID (Integer) assigned to the call by Communication Manager.
    universalCallIdAlways provided Holds the Universal Call ID (Long) assigned to the call by Communication Manager. The Universal Call ID is unique on the switch network because it is combination of switch network node number, call ID, and the time stamp for the call. So this Universal Call ID should be used to identify the call on the CMS report.
    universalCallIdStrAlways provided Holds the Universal Call ID (String) assigned to the call by Communication Manager. The Universal Call ID is unique on the switch network because it is combination of switch network node number, call ID, and the time stamp for the call. So this Universal Call ID should be used to identify the call on the CMS report. The string version of the Universal Call ID matches that provided by Call Control Events.
    so_active Always provided Indicates whether service observing is active for this device or not.
    incoming Always provided Indicates whether this is an incoming call to the requested device or not.
    incomingTrunkCall Always provided Indicates whether this is an outside call coming in from a trunk to the requested device.
    recordingExtension Always provided If the getCallInformation request is for a service observer extension and extension is in a call recordingExtension has the extension that is being observed (or recorded via service observing feature). In other scenarios, this has the extenstion of the call originator. If the call was not originated on the Communication Manager Application Enablebment server is connected to, this has the extension that was in the getCallInformation request.
    recordingExtensionName Always provided The name administered for the recordingExtension.
    vdnExtension Conditional The extension of the VDN that was used to route the call here. If the call is not routed through a VDN extension, then this field is NULL.
    vdnName Conditional The name of the VDN that was used to route the call here. If the call is not routed through a VDN extension, then this field is NULL.
    stateOfCall Not supported
    agentLoginId Conditional This field specifies the login ID of the agent who is logged into the extension given in getGetCallInformation request. If there is a recording extension present (see above), and there is an agent logged into the recording extension, then the recording extension's agent login ID is specified. If there is no agent involved, then this field is NULL.
    agentName Conditional This field specifies the name of the agent who is logged into the extension given in getGetCallInformation request. If there is a recording extension present (see above), and there is an agent logged into the recording extension, then the recording extension's agent name is specified. If there is no agent involved, then this field is NULL.
    agentStationExtension Conditional If an agent is logged into the extension given in getCallInformation request, this specifies the same extension. If there is a recording extension present (see above), and there is an agent logged into the recording extension, then the recording extension is specified. If there is no agent involved, then this field is NULL.
    extensions Not used
    Version:
